## Your Task

Produce a `<patch>` XML document that resolves the identified gaps.

### ⚠️ CRITICAL CONSTRAINTS

- **ONLY reference node/edge IDs that appear in the "Current Argumentation Graph" section above.** Do NOT invent or guess IDs.
- **ONLY use operations defined in the schema below**: `add`, `modify`, `remove`. Inside `<modify><node>`, only use: `add_evidence`, `update_text`, `add_source`. Inside `<modify><edge>`, only use: `update_type`.
- **Do NOT invent operations** such as `remove_source`, `update_evidence`, `replace_node`, `merge`, or anything not listed below.
- **Use `new_` prefix** for new node/edge IDs (e.g. `new_n1`, `new_e1`).
- **All quotes must be exact verbatim substrings** of the source text. Do not paraphrase.

### Allowed XML Schema

```xml
<patch>
  <!-- ADD new nodes and edges -->
  <add>
    <node id="new_n1" type="claim|evidence_quote|counterclaim">
      <text>Node text</text>
      <sources><source>source_id</source></sources>
      <evidence><quote source="source_id">Exact verbatim quote</quote></evidence>
    </node>
    <edge id="new_e1" type="supports|attacks|refines|about|depends_on" from="new_n1" to="existing_node_id"/>
  </add>
  <!-- MODIFY existing nodes/edges (use IDs from graph above) -->
  <modify>
    <node id="existing_node_id">
      <add_evidence><quote source="source_id">Verbatim quote</quote></add_evidence>
      <update_text>Replacement text</update_text>
      <add_source>source_id</add_source>
    </node>
    <edge id="existing_edge_id">
      <update_type>new_edge_type</update_type>
    </edge>
  </modify>
  <!-- REMOVE redundant nodes/edges -->
  <remove>
    <node id="existing_node_id"/>
    <edge id="existing_edge_id"/>
  </remove>
</patch>
```

